{{afc comment|Wikidata entry [[d:Q25104460]] Wikidata name: Takayama Inari Shrine [[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 09:45, 11 June 2025 (UTC)}} {{Infobox religious building | name = Takayama Inari Shrine | native_name = 高山稲荷神社 | image = File:Takayama Inari Shrine.JPG | image_upright = 1.2 | caption = [[Torii]] winding through the grounds of the shrine. | map_type = Japan Aomori Prefecture#Japan | map_alt = | coordinates = {{Coord|40.9385|N|140.31238888889|E|region:JP_type:landmark|display=inline,title}} | map_relief = | map_size = | map_caption = | religious_affiliation = [[Shinto]] | type = | deity ={{ill|Satahiko|qid=Q11304722}}; {{ill|Ukanomitama|qid=Q3080728}}; {{ill|Ōmiyanome|qid=Q24865597}} | founded_by = | established = | date_destroyed = | location = [[:en:Tsugaru, Aomori|Tsugaru]], [[:en:Aomori Prefecture|Aomori]], [[:en:Japan|Japan]] | website = | architecture_style = | festival = | leadership = | location = {{ill|Tsugaru|qid=Q372517}} }} {{nihongo|'''Takayama Inari Shrine'''|高山稲荷神社 |Takayama Inari Jinja}} is a [[:en:Shinto shrine|Shinto shrine]] located in the city of [[:en:Tsugaru, Aomori|Tsugaru]], [[:en:Aomori Prefecture|Aomori Prefecture]], [[:en:Japan|Japan]]. The shrine is dedicated to [[:en:Inari Ōkami|Inari Ōkami]]. Takayama Inari Shrine is notable for the many red [[torii]] that wind along its path. It is said that this shrine had already been established in the late 17th century.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.travel-around-japan.com/k21-14-takayama-inari.html |title=Takayama Inari Shrine (Aomori Prefecture)|website=Let's travel around Japan!}} </ref> Next to the shrine is a memorial dedicated to American sailors who died in 1889 when [[:en:full-rigged ship|full-rigged ship]] ''[[:en:Cheseborough|Cheseborough]]'' wrecked off the coast of [[:en:Shariki, Aomori|Shariki Village]] (now a part of Tsugaru) during a [[:en:Typhoon|Typhoon]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.city.tsugaru.aomori.jp/English/takayama.html |title=Tsugaru City Official English Website - Tsugaru City, Aomori Prefecture, Japan |website=www.city.tsugaru.aomori.jp |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120819201726/http://www.city.tsugaru.aomori.jp/English/takayama.html |archive-date=2012-08-19}} </ref>
